<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841.24/595: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-25T00:00:00-04:00">June 25,
                                        1941—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2294. From Hopkins. Your 2572<note n="51" xml:id="d263fn51">Dated
                                    June 20, 9 p.m., <ref target="#pg_309">p. 309</ref>.</note>
                                regarding shipments of articles for civilian consumption referred to
                                your cable June 20th President consents to such methods of
                                distribution as deemed most practicable by you. [Hopkins.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>